item.description:
Having informally used and discussed functions, it is time to formalize a few concepts.
A function call is the act of using a function by referring to its name, followed by parentheses. A synonymous term is function invocation, and we will sometimes say that we are &ldquo;invoking a function.&rdquo;
Within parentheses, a comma-separated list of arguments may be provided when calling a function. These are sometimes called inputs, and we say that the inputs are &ldquo;passed to&rdquo; the function.
